When Caesar was killed, therefore, he found no common point of sympathy either with those who rejoiced in the death of a tyraut, as did Cicero, or with those who used Caesar’s name to conjure with, as did Antony. His grief at Caesar's death and his superintendence of the public games in his name called forth unfriendly criticism from Cicero.
